    "name": "BCA THCC - Part A",
    "description": "## BCA Take-Home Code Challenge - Part A\n\nThis collection is designed for **testing and prototyping REST API interactions** using the [reqres.in](https://reqres.in) hosted API. It covers two core areas of a typical web application: **user management** and **authentication**.\n\n---\n\n### 👤 Users Requests\n\nContains the full set of CRUD operations for managing users:\n\n| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `GET` | `/api/users?page=2` | Retrieve a paginated list of users |\n| `GET` | `/api/users/{id}` | Fetch a specific user by ID |\n| `POST` | `/api/users` | Create a new user |\n| `PUT` | `/api/users/{id}` | Fully update a user by ID |\n| `PATCH` | `/api/users/{id}` | Partially update a user by ID |\n| `DELETE` | `/api/users/{id}` | Delete a user by ID |\n\n---\n\n### 🔐 Auth Requests\n\nCovers user authentication flows:\n\n| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `POST` | `/api/register` | Register a new user account |\n\n---\n\n> **Note:** All requests target the [reqres.in](https://reqres.in) API — a free, hosted REST API built for front-end and back-end testing and prototyping. No real data is persisted.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "9464946"
  },
